    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Small communities that were typically built to accommodate the workforce of a large employer, often providing a relatively high standard of housing. Prime examples are those constructed from the late 18th century onwards by industrialists to house their workers near the factory site.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
